headline: Wells Fargo Taps JPMorgan Executive to Lead Its Credit-Card Business
summary: Wells Fargo  has hired  JPMorgan  Chase executive Ed Olebe to lead its credit-card business, people familiar with the matter said.  The bank is trying to grow that business under CEO Charlie Scharf.  Olebe left JPMorgan late last year and will soon take over for Ray Fischer, who is set to retire, the people said.
